              <h3>Summary</h3>

              <p>SAD or Sistema de Alerta de Desmatemento is a monthly deforestation alert system that monitors increments of forest degradation and deforestation in the Brazilian Amazon. The information the systems generates is published monthly by Imazon, a Brazilian NGO, through the Forest Transparency bulletin. The monthly alerts are derived from a temporal mosaic of MODIS (Moderate Resolution Imaging Spectroradiometer) daily images that are scaled down from 500-meter to 250-meter. The monthly results are also validated using more detailed images from the China-Brazil Earth Resource Satellite (CBERS) and NASA Landsat data.</p>

